WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.080
Trip and I are going
to the movies tonight.

00:03.080 --> 00:04.540
Cooper and I
are going, too.

00:04.540 --> 00:05.960
Oh, cool! I like movies.
Maybe I'll tag along.

00:05.960 --> 00:08.000
Sorry, I misspoke.
I meant mini-golf.
Yeah, me, too.

00:08.000 --> 00:09.620
Oh, I like mini-golf.

00:09.620 --> 00:10.920
What do you not like, Dad?
Because we're doing that.

00:10.920 --> 00:12.170
Yeah, me, too.

00:12.170 --> 00:14.290
All right, you go.
Have fun.

00:14.290 --> 00:15.620
Anna-Kat, hurry up.
You're gonna be late.

00:15.620 --> 00:17.250
Where's your backpack?
Upstairs.

00:17.250 --> 00:18.420
I'll get it.

00:18.420 --> 00:20.330
Quick, finish your breakfast.
Bigger bites.

00:20.330 --> 00:21.750
Put it down like a snake.

00:21.750 --> 00:30.540
♪♪

00:30.540 --> 00:31.880
[ Sighs ]

00:31.880 --> 00:32.830
Where's your sweatshirt?

00:32.830 --> 00:34.750
Next to my backpack.

00:34.750 --> 00:36.580
[ Exhales sharply ]

00:36.580 --> 00:44.830
♪♪

00:44.830 --> 00:46.500
[ Sighs ]

00:46.500 --> 00:49.080
Anna-Kat, you're only wearing
one sneaker.

00:50.620 --> 00:51.670
Oh, yeah.

00:51.670 --> 00:53.040
♪♪

00:53.040 --> 00:54.500
[ Sighs ]

00:54.500 --> 00:59.920
♪♪

00:59.920 --> 01:03.250
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:03.250 --> 01:08.580
♪♪

01:08.580 --> 01:09.120
Catch!

01:12.710 --> 01:13.620
[ Exhales deeply ]

01:13.620 --> 01:15.290
Are you okay?

01:15.290 --> 01:16.460
[ Sighs ]

01:16.460 --> 01:19.420
I know I am this close
to turning 40,

01:19.420 --> 01:21.380
but I don't think
that I can blame age

01:21.380 --> 01:23.670
for getting tired
halfway up the stairs.

01:23.670 --> 01:25.290
Blame me.
I'm a very easy target.

01:25.290 --> 01:28.170
I just don't love how I feel
in my body right now.

01:28.170 --> 01:30.120
I don't feel attractive.

01:30.120 --> 01:32.460
I might need
to change some things up.

01:32.460 --> 01:34.420
I like how you are
right now.

01:34.420 --> 01:36.000
But if you feel like
you should change,

01:36.000 --> 01:37.790
then you should go ahead
and make that change.

01:37.790 --> 01:39.170
And I'm sure
that if you make the change

01:39.170 --> 01:40.290
that I'd like
the new you

01:40.290 --> 01:41.580
as much as I like
the current you,

01:41.580 --> 01:42.750
as you are.

01:42.750 --> 01:43.920
Currently.

01:45.290 --> 01:47.380
I wasn't fishing
for a nervous compliment, Greg.

01:47.380 --> 01:49.120
I'm just
making a statement.

01:49.120 --> 01:51.120
Oh.

01:51.120 --> 01:52.960
Do you think you could
take the kids to school?

01:52.960 --> 01:54.580
I'm just gonna stay here.

01:54.580 --> 01:56.210
I know
it's only 8:00 a.m.,

01:56.210 --> 01:58.460
but I feel like
I've done enough.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
♪♪

02:05.620 --> 02:07.830
[ Knock on door ]

02:07.830 --> 02:10.170
Doris' husband, Richard,
is here to see you.

02:10.170 --> 02:11.500
That's weird.

02:11.500 --> 02:12.620
Send him in, I guess.

02:13.920 --> 02:15.750
Hey, Angela.
Hey.

02:15.750 --> 02:17.620
Sorry to just
pop in like this,

02:17.620 --> 02:20.500
but I'm wondering if I can...
talk to you about a situation.

02:20.500 --> 02:21.790
Ah.

02:21.790 --> 02:23.790
Okay, Richard,
let's hear it.

02:23.790 --> 02:25.790
I don't know why,
but because I'm a lesbian,

02:25.790 --> 02:28.420
everyone wants to tell me
their one gay experience, so...

02:28.420 --> 02:29.540
come on.

02:29.540 --> 02:30.330
No.

02:30.330 --> 02:31.790
I'm going to
divorce Doris,

02:31.790 --> 02:33.830
and I'd like to hire you
as my lawyer.

02:33.830 --> 02:35.380
What?
Oh! [ Laughs ]

02:35.380 --> 02:36.790
Hell no!

02:36.790 --> 02:39.170
I am not representing you if
you're divorcing my best friend.

02:39.170 --> 02:40.170
I figured as much.

02:40.170 --> 02:41.500
But now that
I've talked to you,

02:41.500 --> 02:43.750
legally, you can't
represent her against me.

02:43.750 --> 02:44.960
Thanks so much
for your help.

02:44.960 --> 02:50.880
♪♪

02:50.880 --> 02:52.960
[ Sighs ]
Is this a real emergency,

02:52.960 --> 02:54.540
or do you just throw "911"
on a text

02:54.540 --> 02:56.210
like when my kids
run out

02:56.210 --> 02:58.040
of those little
Trader Joe's ice cream cones?

02:58.040 --> 03:00.080
Richard is
divorcing Doris.

03:00.080 --> 03:01.380
What?

03:01.380 --> 03:03.120
He came to my office today
to talk to me

03:03.120 --> 03:04.540
so that Doris couldn't
hire me as her lawyer.

03:04.540 --> 03:05.790
[ Gasps ]

03:05.790 --> 03:07.000
Meryl Streep's lawyer

03:07.000 --> 03:09.080
told her to do that
on "Big Little Lies"!

03:09.080 --> 03:10.540
I know. What'd you think
of her teeth?

03:10.540 --> 03:11.790
I found them distracting.

03:11.790 --> 03:13.080
See, I thought
they made her character.

03:13.080 --> 03:14.460
We're getting off track.
Right.

03:14.460 --> 03:15.750
Listen,
we need to figure out

03:15.750 --> 03:17.380
how we're gonna play this
when Doris tells us

03:17.380 --> 03:19.080
because she's probably
gonna be a total mess.

03:19.080 --> 03:20.710
Hey!
What's up, bitches?

03:20.710 --> 03:22.170
Oh!
There she is!

03:22.170 --> 03:23.380
Hey, girl.

03:23.380 --> 03:25.080
So, what are we
talking about?

03:25.080 --> 03:27.460
Oh, you know, the usual.

03:27.460 --> 03:30.620
Greg, blah, blah, blah,
my kids, nyeh, nyeh, nyeh.

03:30.620 --> 03:33.290
I'm gay. [ Chuckles ]
[ Chuckles ]

03:33.290 --> 03:34.750
You guys are being weird.
Why are you being weird?

03:34.750 --> 03:35.830
Who's acting weird?

03:35.830 --> 03:37.000
I am gay.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.460
[ Nervous laughter ]

03:39.460 --> 03:43.000
So, Doris...
anything new?

03:43.000 --> 03:44.580
Oh!

03:44.580 --> 03:46.380
I think I might be done brushing
my teeth in the morning.

03:46.380 --> 03:47.880
Now I just chew gum
and go like this.

03:48.830 --> 03:50.500
That's neat.

03:50.500 --> 03:52.580
I'm gonna step out real quick
to use the bathroom.

03:52.580 --> 04:02.290
♪♪

04:02.290 --> 04:03.380
I gotta poop.

04:03.380 --> 04:08.750
♪♪

04:08.750 --> 04:10.580
[ Sighs ]
She doesn't know.

04:10.580 --> 04:12.000
Well,
we have to tell her.

04:12.000 --> 04:13.330
Richard told you.
You tell her.

04:13.330 --> 04:15.000
No!
I sit next to her.

04:15.000 --> 04:16.880
I am within
fork-stabbing distance.

04:16.880 --> 04:19.330
And you know Doris does not
react well to bad news.

04:19.330 --> 04:20.210
[ Groans ]

04:21.920 --> 04:22.670
Sorry about that.

04:22.670 --> 04:24.000
Everything good?

04:24.000 --> 04:25.420
So good.
[ Chuckles ]

04:25.420 --> 04:27.790
Angela, did you have
any interesting visitors

04:27.790 --> 04:29.710
at the office
this morning?

04:29.710 --> 04:32.500
Oh, Katie,
work is so boring.

04:32.500 --> 04:34.000
Let's talk about gossip.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.620
Have you heard anything gossipy
this morning?

04:36.620 --> 04:40.290
♪♪

04:40.290 --> 04:43.040
Would you excuse me
one more time?

04:43.040 --> 04:45.830
♪♪

04:45.830 --> 04:47.580
[ Chuckles ]

04:47.580 --> 04:48.580
♪♪

04:48.580 --> 04:49.880
Part two.

04:49.880 --> 04:52.580
♪♪

04:52.580 --> 04:54.670
You need to cool it
on that flaxseed.

04:56.380 --> 04:58.210
I thought
you were gonna tell her.
I thought you were!

04:58.210 --> 05:00.080
Well, you've known her
longer and --

05:00.080 --> 05:01.250
One, two, three,
not it!

05:03.120 --> 05:04.540
What the hell
is going on?

05:04.540 --> 05:06.960
Are you guys doing
bathroom drugs without me?

05:06.960 --> 05:08.540
Because that would be
so mean!

05:08.540 --> 05:11.710
Doris...I think
you should sit down.

05:13.250 --> 05:14.170
Come on.

05:18.290 --> 05:20.960
There's no easy way
to say this.

05:23.080 --> 05:24.580
Richard is
leaving you.

05:24.580 --> 05:26.170
[ Laughs ]

05:26.170 --> 05:29.170
Yeah, right.
I wish!

05:29.170 --> 05:30.790
No.
No, we're serious.

05:30.790 --> 05:32.960
He came to see me
at the office today

05:32.960 --> 05:34.580
so that
I couldn't represent you.

05:36.040 --> 05:37.460
Like in "Big Little Lies."

05:37.460 --> 05:39.540
We're so sorry, honey.

05:39.540 --> 05:46.080
♪♪

05:46.080 --> 05:47.460
Doris. Doris!

05:47.460 --> 05:48.580
Sorry.

05:48.580 --> 05:49.500
Doris!

05:49.500 --> 05:51.380
[ Breathing heavily ]

05:51.380 --> 05:53.460
You keep chasing her!

05:53.460 --> 05:55.750
I'll wait here
in case she circles back.

05:57.420 --> 05:58.670
[ Exhales deeply ]

05:58.670 --> 06:00.250
♪♪

06:00.250 --> 06:02.080
Greg: 10 years ago,
the kids and I

06:02.080 --> 06:04.580
were making a surprise cake
for Katie's 30th birthday.

06:04.580 --> 06:06.500
Katie came home early,
caught us in the act,

06:06.500 --> 06:08.170
and took this photo.

06:08.170 --> 06:09.960
It's amazing
what you guys can pull off

06:09.960 --> 06:12.040
without a pastry chef
and staff photographer.

06:12.040 --> 06:13.750
It's Katie's
favorite picture.

06:13.750 --> 06:16.040
So I thought for her
40th birthday in a few months,

06:16.040 --> 06:17.790
it'd be fun
to re-create this photo.

06:17.790 --> 06:20.330
A nice homemade gift to
remind her how much we love her.

06:20.330 --> 06:21.620
I'm in.

06:21.620 --> 06:23.420
Trip, you...weren't
in the original picture.

06:23.420 --> 06:25.380
Yeah,
but I'm really photogenic.

06:25.380 --> 06:26.880
Check it.

06:26.880 --> 06:28.290
I'm checking it.

06:28.290 --> 06:30.330
When I'm 32,
you'll be 41.

06:33.120 --> 06:34.920
I got all the props.

06:34.920 --> 06:38.250
And I made a Babybjorn
out of a backpack

06:38.250 --> 06:39.830
and two seatbelts
for Anna-Kat.

06:41.290 --> 06:43.040
[ Scoffs ] There's no way
that thing will hold Anna-Kat.

06:43.040 --> 06:44.120
Don't be so negative.

06:44.120 --> 06:45.670
Then who am I?

06:47.170 --> 06:49.210
We just have to pick a
night when Mom's not home
so we can take the picture.

06:49.210 --> 06:50.460
But she's always home.

06:50.460 --> 06:52.580
She's like that B.O. smell
in Oliver's room.

06:52.580 --> 06:53.670
She refuses to leave.

06:53.670 --> 06:55.880
Fake news.

06:55.880 --> 06:58.080
Oliver, you're wrong.
This'll totally hold her.

07:01.790 --> 07:05.040
♪♪

07:05.040 --> 07:07.420
So, they're
getting divorced?

07:07.420 --> 07:09.580
What did Doris do
that finally made him leave her?

07:09.580 --> 07:11.960
Why do you assume
it was Doris?

07:11.960 --> 07:13.170
[ Door opens ]
For the same reason
if we get divorced,

07:13.170 --> 07:14.210
people will assume
it was you.

07:14.210 --> 07:16.040
[ Door closes ]
That's fair.

07:18.540 --> 07:19.830
W-What are you doing?

07:19.830 --> 07:20.830
I'm exercising.

07:20.830 --> 07:22.000
Oh.

07:22.000 --> 07:24.380
Thanks for trying
to make me laugh.

07:24.380 --> 07:27.000
Well, you were right.

07:27.000 --> 07:28.420
Richard's leaving me.

07:28.420 --> 07:29.960
I found papers
on the kitchen table.

07:29.960 --> 07:31.540
I'm sorry, Doris.

07:31.540 --> 07:33.420
You know, I-I can't believe
this is happening.

07:33.420 --> 07:34.920
I always joked
about me leaving Richard,

07:34.920 --> 07:36.380
but I never thought
in a million years

07:36.380 --> 07:37.790
that he'd be the one
leaving me.

07:37.790 --> 07:40.420
Honey,
I know it's so hard.

07:40.420 --> 07:42.210
I know
he's sleeping with someone.

07:42.210 --> 07:43.790
But it can't be
one of the nannies.

07:43.790 --> 07:46.120
No. I'm no dummy,
I went old and ugly.

07:46.120 --> 07:47.620
Well, you never know.

07:47.620 --> 07:50.460
Oprah says it's not about
how the other woman looks.

07:50.460 --> 07:52.540
It's about
how she makes your man feel.

07:54.380 --> 07:55.500
What are you doing?

07:56.830 --> 07:58.830
If he's sleeping with someone,
so will I.

07:58.830 --> 08:00.460
We're going out tonight.

08:00.460 --> 08:02.210
You and Angela are gonna be
my wing women.

08:02.210 --> 08:03.210
[ Chuckles ]

08:03.210 --> 08:04.830
I've got to find
a dude to bone.

08:07.170 --> 08:08.620
No.

08:08.620 --> 08:09.710
♪♪

08:13.380 --> 08:17.080
♪♪

08:17.080 --> 08:18.750
Wow!
You look fantastic.

08:21.210 --> 08:22.330
I'm gonna call Doris
and lie

08:22.330 --> 08:24.170
and tell her
one of our idiot kids got lice

08:24.170 --> 08:26.000
and now we all have it.

08:26.000 --> 08:28.540
Actually, that's not a lie.
We probably all do.

08:28.540 --> 08:30.170
I know you don't feel so great
about yourself right now,

08:30.170 --> 08:32.210
but trust me,
you're a catch.

08:32.210 --> 08:34.670
I bet if you didn't have
that ring on, guys would
hit on you all night long.

08:34.670 --> 08:35.880
You're just saying that.

08:35.880 --> 08:37.750
Well...let's find out.

08:39.460 --> 08:42.670
Katie Otto, will you un-marry me
for one night?

08:42.670 --> 08:44.290
Aww.

08:47.250 --> 08:49.620
Just to be clear,
does this actually mean I can --

08:49.620 --> 08:50.670
No!

08:50.670 --> 08:52.620
Good thing I checked.
Mm-hmm.

08:52.620 --> 08:55.250
♪♪

08:55.250 --> 08:57.290
[ Vehicle departs ]

08:57.290 --> 08:59.330
Okay, Mom's gone!

08:59.330 --> 09:00.710
Oliver!
Get down here!

09:00.710 --> 09:02.670
Taylor, Mom's finally
out of the house.

09:02.670 --> 09:04.670
Get out the mixing bowls
and start making the batter.

09:04.670 --> 09:06.920
We need everything to
look exactly like it did
in the original picture.

09:06.920 --> 09:08.290
Go throw on
your ducky pajamas.

09:08.290 --> 09:09.710
Dad, we told you.
Cooper and I have plans.

09:09.710 --> 09:11.170
So do me and Trip.

09:11.170 --> 09:12.710
Well, you're gonna
have to cancel.

09:12.710 --> 09:14.170
We might not get
another chance.

09:14.170 --> 09:15.500
We can't cancel.

09:15.500 --> 09:17.580
It's opening night
of the new "Terminator" movie.

09:17.580 --> 09:19.620
If we don't go,
people will ruin it for us.

09:19.620 --> 09:21.500
But if we do go,
we can ruin it for other people.

09:21.500 --> 09:23.290
Oliver: Besides,
you signed off on it.

09:23.290 --> 09:24.620
You're always prattling on

09:24.620 --> 09:26.830
about how important it is
to be a man of your word.

09:26.830 --> 09:29.620
Should we just ignore everything
else you've taught us?

09:29.620 --> 09:32.120
Yeah. So should I chat
with strangers on the Internet?

09:37.170 --> 09:39.210
You just got outsmarted
by Taylor.

09:39.210 --> 09:40.670
That can't feel good.

09:40.670 --> 09:42.620
Not necessarily.

09:42.620 --> 09:44.380
Taylor and Oliver are gonna be
grounded for the night.

09:44.380 --> 09:45.920
I just
have to figure out why.

09:45.920 --> 09:47.710
Ooh, shady parenting.

09:47.710 --> 09:49.750
This is usually
Mom's department.

09:49.750 --> 09:51.040
You just got interesting.

09:52.290 --> 09:56.170
[ Indistinct talking,
dance music playing ]

09:56.170 --> 09:58.210
Oh, this is amazing!

09:58.210 --> 10:00.120
Why didn't I do this
a long time ago?!

10:00.120 --> 10:01.750
Because you were married!

10:01.750 --> 10:02.790
[ Laughter ]

10:02.790 --> 10:04.750
[ Women laughing ]

10:04.750 --> 10:11.920
♪♪

10:11.920 --> 10:13.330
Hi, ladies.

10:13.330 --> 10:16.830
My friend just found out
she's getting divorced,

10:16.830 --> 10:18.750
and this is kind of
her big night out.

10:18.750 --> 10:23.290
So our group are the ones
who need to have the most fun.

10:23.290 --> 10:25.210
Yeah, so we're gonna have to
ask you to leave.

10:25.210 --> 10:26.000
Mm-hmm.

10:27.120 --> 10:28.250
No.

10:28.250 --> 10:30.330
♪♪

10:30.330 --> 10:32.420
I'll give you 500 bucks.

10:32.420 --> 10:34.500
And an extra 50
for those boas and the tiaras.

10:34.500 --> 10:35.670
♪♪

10:35.670 --> 10:36.960
[ Laughter ]

10:36.960 --> 10:38.170
Here we go!

10:39.750 --> 10:41.670
Whoo!
Oh, yeah!

10:41.670 --> 10:43.880
All right,
who wants to make out?!

10:43.880 --> 10:45.210
Ow, ow, ow,
ow, ow, ow.

10:45.210 --> 10:46.330
[ Laughter ]

10:46.330 --> 10:49.580
♪♪

10:49.580 --> 10:51.500
Taylor, close the fridge door,
please.

10:51.500 --> 10:53.460
I'll close it in a sec.
I got my hands full.

10:55.380 --> 10:56.790
When you leave
the door open,

10:56.790 --> 10:58.960
the fridge thinks it needs
to cool the entire house.

10:58.960 --> 11:01.750
I'm just doing my part
to counteract global warming.

11:01.750 --> 11:02.830
Was that attitude?

11:02.830 --> 11:04.000
Total attitude.

11:04.000 --> 11:05.580
No, no. I --

11:05.580 --> 11:06.960
For the first time, I think
I was actually being clever.

11:06.960 --> 11:08.080
You're grounded.

11:08.080 --> 11:10.380
No movie for you tonight.
What?!

11:10.380 --> 11:11.580
And since you're grounded
for the night,

11:11.580 --> 11:13.420
now you'll be able
to take that picture after all.

11:13.420 --> 11:15.250
[ Sighs ]
You've got to be kidding me.

11:18.460 --> 11:19.580
If you'll excuse us,

11:19.580 --> 11:21.330
Cooper and I are gonna
go up to my room

11:21.330 --> 11:23.000
and sit silently
with our hands folded

11:23.000 --> 11:24.330
until the movie starts.

11:27.920 --> 11:29.250
He's onto us.

11:29.250 --> 11:30.330
I know.

11:30.330 --> 11:31.620
We have Taylor,

11:31.620 --> 11:33.750
but if we don't have Oliver,
we don't have a picture.

11:33.750 --> 11:34.620
What's the plan?

11:34.620 --> 11:36.040
I'm gonna
bust into his room,

11:36.040 --> 11:37.750
see if I can find
a groundable offense.

11:37.750 --> 11:40.120
Top-left desk drawer.
Check his journal.

11:40.120 --> 11:41.620
Some pretty meaty stuff
in there.

11:41.620 --> 11:43.710
Hmm.

11:43.710 --> 11:49.460
♪♪

11:49.460 --> 11:55.210
♪♪

11:55.210 --> 11:58.210
So, uh...
you the bride-to-be?

11:58.210 --> 11:59.040
Sorry?

12:00.380 --> 12:01.670
Oh.

12:01.670 --> 12:03.210
This? No.

12:03.210 --> 12:04.790
My friend
is getting a divorce,

12:04.790 --> 12:06.790
and so we're trying
to help her find someone

12:06.790 --> 12:08.460
to have
a revenge hook-up with.

12:08.460 --> 12:10.580
Ohh.
That is so sweet.

12:10.580 --> 12:11.620
[ Chuckles ]

12:11.620 --> 12:12.670
How about you?

12:12.670 --> 12:14.330
What?

12:14.330 --> 12:17.540
You looking for anybody
to have a revenge hook-up with?

12:17.540 --> 12:21.420
[ Laughs ]

12:21.420 --> 12:23.040
Wait a minute.

12:23.040 --> 12:24.790
You're Malcolm Smith.

12:24.790 --> 12:26.580
You recognize me?

12:26.580 --> 12:28.210
Of course!

12:28.210 --> 12:30.880
I saw you score, like, 30 points
in that all-star game.

12:30.880 --> 12:32.710
Well, I'm only hoping
to score once tonight.

12:32.710 --> 12:34.290
[ Laughs ]

12:34.290 --> 12:35.710
[ Chuckles ]

12:35.710 --> 12:37.710
Malcolm Smith.

12:37.710 --> 12:38.620
Are you hitting on me?

12:38.620 --> 12:40.170
Yes.

12:40.170 --> 12:41.040
Yes, I am.

12:42.460 --> 12:43.750
Why?

12:43.750 --> 12:45.170
What do you mean, "Why?"

12:45.170 --> 12:48.540
You're hot,
you know sports,

12:48.540 --> 12:52.210
and I don't see a wedding ring,
so I'm assuming single.

12:53.500 --> 12:55.830
Look...at...this.

12:55.830 --> 12:57.120
[ Chuckles ]

12:57.120 --> 12:58.500
Unfortunately, I'm married.

12:58.500 --> 13:00.330
I mean,
it's not unfortunate.

13:00.330 --> 13:02.500
I love my husband
very much.

13:03.750 --> 13:05.290
Sometimes it's unfortunate.

13:05.290 --> 13:06.210
[ Chuckles ]

13:08.000 --> 13:09.790
Well, uh...

13:09.790 --> 13:10.960
if you...

13:10.960 --> 13:12.500
[ Pen clicks ]

13:12.500 --> 13:15.750
...if you ever change your mind,
I would love to...

13:15.750 --> 13:18.210
just give you
a little piggyback ride.

13:18.210 --> 13:20.040
It's quite the view.

13:21.000 --> 13:23.420
So is this.

13:23.420 --> 13:29.750
♪♪

13:29.750 --> 13:31.920
Hello, Father.
To what do we owe the pleasure?

13:31.920 --> 13:34.830
I was just...
popping in to say hello.

13:34.830 --> 13:36.120
Making sure
everything is...

13:36.120 --> 13:37.210
in order!

13:38.960 --> 13:41.830
Hospital corners.
Very nice.

13:41.830 --> 13:43.040
Just like you taught me.

13:43.040 --> 13:44.500
One of the many
priceless lessons

13:44.500 --> 13:46.290
I will carry with me
out into this world.

13:46.290 --> 13:48.710
We figured
with Oliver's room so clean

13:48.710 --> 13:50.620
and all of his many chores
completed,

13:50.620 --> 13:52.750
it'd be a nice time to start
reading your book aloud.

13:52.750 --> 13:54.170
How wonderful.

13:54.170 --> 13:55.250
You boys
enjoy your reading.

13:55.250 --> 13:56.330
We sure will.

13:56.330 --> 13:57.960
My only critique
of the book --

13:57.960 --> 13:59.500
it's not long enough.

13:59.500 --> 14:00.500
Yeah, yeah.

14:00.500 --> 14:03.040
♪♪

14:03.040 --> 14:04.960
[ Dance music plays ]

14:04.960 --> 14:07.620
♪♪

14:07.620 --> 14:09.040
[ Slurps ]

14:11.580 --> 14:12.790
What about that guy?

14:12.790 --> 14:14.500
♪♪

14:14.500 --> 14:17.330
He's in a three-piece suit
and looks constipated.

14:17.330 --> 14:18.710
He's like
a white Richard.

14:18.710 --> 14:20.170
[ Laughs ]

14:20.170 --> 14:21.250
Okay.

14:21.250 --> 14:23.080
♪♪

14:23.080 --> 14:24.620
How about that one?

14:24.620 --> 14:26.290
Oh! He is pretty.

14:26.290 --> 14:27.170
Mm-hmm.

14:27.170 --> 14:29.120
I like pretty.

14:29.120 --> 14:31.170
[ Chuckles ]
Time to go in
for the kill.

14:31.170 --> 14:32.960
[ Sighing ] Okay.
Right. Come here.

14:32.960 --> 14:34.790
Take this off.
[ Sighs ]

14:34.790 --> 14:36.330
Go do it.
You got 'im.

14:36.330 --> 14:42.920
♪♪

14:42.920 --> 14:44.500
"Go in for the kill"?

14:44.500 --> 14:46.790
What is happening
with my life?

14:46.790 --> 14:48.080
You know, three nights ago,

14:48.080 --> 14:49.460
I was lying in bed
next to my husband

14:49.460 --> 14:51.670
watching TV shows
on separate computers.

14:53.000 --> 14:54.790
What am I even doing here?

14:54.790 --> 14:57.710
Getting back at Richard
for cheating.

14:57.710 --> 14:59.580
Richard's not cheating,
okay?

14:59.580 --> 15:01.420
I confronted him
before I left the house.

15:01.420 --> 15:02.960
There's --
There's no one else.

15:02.960 --> 15:05.420
Oh, he's lying to cover his ass
for the divorce.

15:05.420 --> 15:07.460
No, that's not it.

15:07.460 --> 15:09.540
♪♪

15:09.540 --> 15:11.830
He said he doesn't
enjoy my company anymore.

15:11.830 --> 15:12.540
What?

15:12.540 --> 15:14.920
Yeah.

15:14.920 --> 15:17.460
He said he'd rather be all alone
than be with me.

15:19.000 --> 15:20.880
Am I really that awful?

15:20.880 --> 15:23.460
♪♪

15:23.460 --> 15:25.380
I knew it.
I am that awful.

15:25.380 --> 15:26.670
♪♪

15:26.670 --> 15:28.170
Why didn't you
say something?
Why didn't you?

15:28.170 --> 15:29.620
And lie to our friend?

15:29.620 --> 15:31.120
That's all you do!
Oh, God!

15:34.330 --> 15:37.670
Doris, obviously,
we don't think you're awful.

15:37.670 --> 15:38.880
Are you difficult?

15:38.880 --> 15:40.290
Yeah.
Yeah.

15:40.290 --> 15:42.620
But you're
an amazing person, too.

15:42.620 --> 15:45.120
You know this whole situation
is really more about Richard.

15:45.120 --> 15:46.790
If he doesn't love
everything about you,

15:46.790 --> 15:48.620
then you're probably
better off without him.

15:48.620 --> 15:50.330
Yeah.
To hell with Richard!

15:50.330 --> 15:52.580
Let's throw all the suits
in his Aston Martin

15:52.580 --> 15:53.710
and set it on fire!

15:53.710 --> 15:55.170
[ Laughter ]

15:55.170 --> 15:56.540
Thank you, guys.
Oh, honey.

15:56.540 --> 15:58.000
Mm.

15:59.540 --> 16:03.790
You know, I've been with Richard
for so long,

16:03.790 --> 16:05.790
I've forgotten what it's like
to be alone.

16:05.790 --> 16:06.880
Oh, it's awesome.

16:06.880 --> 16:08.540
You get to sleep diagonally
in bed,

16:08.540 --> 16:10.210
you don't have to have sex
with the same person

16:10.210 --> 16:11.580
over and over
and over again,

16:11.580 --> 16:13.790
and you only get your kids
half the time.

16:13.790 --> 16:14.790
[ Chuckles ]
Ugh.

16:14.790 --> 16:17.420
Being in a good marriage
is so unfair.

16:17.420 --> 16:19.710
I can't take a piggyback ride
on Malcolm Smith,

16:19.710 --> 16:22.000
and I have my kids
the whole stupid time!

16:22.000 --> 16:23.250
Oh, you poor thing.
Aww.

16:23.250 --> 16:24.830
We're here for you.
Yeah.

16:24.830 --> 16:26.750
[ Laughter ]

16:26.750 --> 16:30.380
♪♪

16:30.380 --> 16:31.540
We're off to the movies.

16:31.540 --> 16:32.960
But it doesn't start
for another hour.

16:32.960 --> 16:34.210
Oh,
we're heading out early

16:34.210 --> 16:35.670
so we can drive
well under the speed limit.

16:35.670 --> 16:36.670
Safety first.

16:36.670 --> 16:38.420
I'm transporting
precious cargo here.

16:38.420 --> 16:40.580
Have a great night,
everybody.

16:40.580 --> 16:41.750
[ Sighs ]

16:41.750 --> 16:43.170
I love you, Dad.

16:43.170 --> 16:44.250
Hold on.

16:44.250 --> 16:46.290
I love you, too, son.

16:47.830 --> 16:49.580
What's thi-- What?

16:50.750 --> 16:52.000
Well, well, well.

16:52.000 --> 16:54.250
What do we have here?

16:54.250 --> 16:56.420
Oliver,
is this marijuana?

16:56.420 --> 16:58.170
Oh, my.

16:58.170 --> 16:59.250
You're grounded.

16:59.250 --> 17:00.290
I'm being framed.

17:00.290 --> 17:02.170
We both know
you planted this on me.

17:02.170 --> 17:04.120
I mean, this jacket
doesn't even have pockets!

17:04.120 --> 17:05.620
No movie for you tonight.

17:05.620 --> 17:07.290
No way!
That's so messed up!

17:07.290 --> 17:08.420
We're still going.

17:08.420 --> 17:09.830
Okay, Oliver, wait.

17:09.830 --> 17:12.290
This is clearly important
to Dad.

17:12.290 --> 17:13.710
And after everything
he's done for us,

17:13.710 --> 17:15.210
I think
we owe it to him

17:15.210 --> 17:17.380
to stop thinking
about ourselves for once

17:17.380 --> 17:20.000
and just stay home
and take the picture.

17:21.380 --> 17:22.210
Fine.

17:26.000 --> 17:27.880
Who gave this to you?
I'll kill them.

17:27.880 --> 17:29.670
It's Italian seasoning.

17:29.670 --> 17:31.460
Oh, is that what
they're calling it these days?

17:31.460 --> 17:32.960
Hmm?

17:32.960 --> 17:37.040
♪♪

17:37.040 --> 17:38.460
Okay, Taylor,

17:38.460 --> 17:41.080
just a smidge more batter
on your forehead.

17:41.080 --> 17:42.460
Greg:
How's it looking?

17:42.460 --> 17:43.250
All set.

17:44.580 --> 17:45.620
This is awesome.

17:45.620 --> 17:46.960
When I get married,

17:46.960 --> 17:49.420
I'm making you walk me
down the aisle like this.

17:49.420 --> 17:50.620
Oliver, you ready?

17:52.380 --> 17:54.830
Aww! Look who's up
past his bedtime.

17:54.830 --> 17:56.830
[ Laughs ]
Greg: I appreciate you guys
making this happen.

17:56.830 --> 17:59.330
It means a lot to me, and it's
gonna mean a lot to your mom.

17:59.330 --> 18:01.000
Come on, guys!
Have some fun with it.

18:01.000 --> 18:04.420
[ Laughter ]

18:04.420 --> 18:06.000
Oh!

18:06.000 --> 18:07.290
Uh, Taylor,
tongue out.

18:08.500 --> 18:10.000
Oliver, uh,
lick the frosting.

18:11.000 --> 18:12.250
Mr. Otto, um,
act surprised.

18:13.380 --> 18:15.620
Three, two, one.

18:16.620 --> 18:18.620
Perfect.

18:18.620 --> 18:20.790
I wish life was this fun
when I got grounded.

18:20.790 --> 18:22.830
I wish I had parents around
to ground me at all.

18:22.830 --> 18:24.580
Hey, why don't you guys
jump in here?

18:24.580 --> 18:26.960
Then in 10 years,
we'll re-create this one, too.

18:26.960 --> 18:28.330
Really?
Yeah.

18:28.330 --> 18:30.330
You guys are gonna be around
a long time. Come on.

18:30.330 --> 18:33.580
♪♪

18:33.580 --> 18:35.620
Setting the timer.

18:35.620 --> 18:37.540
[ Beeping ]
Three...

18:37.540 --> 18:38.960
two, one!

18:38.960 --> 18:40.580
[ Laughs ]

18:40.580 --> 18:41.960
[ Beep, camera shutter clicks ]

18:41.960 --> 18:45.120
Wait. Can we take another one?
Because I want a copy.

18:45.120 --> 18:47.170
Trip,
you know you can just --

18:47.170 --> 18:48.540
Let's take another one
for Trip.

18:48.540 --> 18:52.330
♪♪

18:52.330 --> 18:54.420
[ Door opens, closes ]

18:54.420 --> 18:58.040
♪♪

18:58.040 --> 19:00.000
So...
did you meet anyone?

19:00.000 --> 19:01.500
Oh, I don't know.

19:01.500 --> 19:05.120
Does the name Malcolm Smith
mean anything to you?

19:05.120 --> 19:06.830
Does the name
Gerard Manley Hopkins

19:06.830 --> 19:08.210
mean anything to you?

19:08.210 --> 19:10.250
See how it feels
when you ask someone

19:10.250 --> 19:12.330
if they know someone
you know they don't know?

19:12.330 --> 19:14.210
He's a pro
basketball player.

19:14.210 --> 19:15.830
And he thought
I was hot.

19:15.830 --> 19:17.420
Ohh!
Tell me all about it.

19:17.420 --> 19:20.960
Well, he came up to me
at the bar,

19:20.960 --> 19:22.670
and we talked a bit,

19:22.670 --> 19:25.790
and then he said
he'd like to, you know...

19:25.790 --> 19:28.000
♪ Bow-chicki-bow-bowww ♪

19:28.000 --> 19:30.540
♪ Mama-na-nanananananana ♪

19:30.540 --> 19:31.670
Ah! Nice!

19:31.670 --> 19:33.380
Suck it,
motherhood and time!

19:33.380 --> 19:35.380
[ Laughs ] Sweet.

19:35.380 --> 19:37.380
Thanks for making me
get back out there.

19:37.380 --> 19:39.380
I may not
be feeling my best,

19:39.380 --> 19:43.080
but it's nice to know
I still got it.

19:43.080 --> 19:44.960
As far as I'm concerned,
you've always had it.

19:48.250 --> 19:50.040
You still enjoy my company,
right?

19:50.040 --> 19:52.330
Of course. Always.

19:52.330 --> 19:53.420
Just checking.

19:53.420 --> 19:54.460
[ Chuckles ]

19:58.670 --> 20:00.250
Is that the basketball
player's number?

20:00.250 --> 20:01.040
Yep.
Mm.

20:07.580 --> 20:09.170
[ Whirring ]

20:11.960 --> 20:13.620
[ Whirring continues ]

20:13.620 --> 20:16.920
♪♪

20:20.120 --> 20:22.170
[ Laughter ]

20:22.170 --> 20:24.000
So, you just swipe through
until you find someone you like.

20:24.000 --> 20:25.380
Ooh!
Look at all these choices.

20:25.380 --> 20:26.920
All sorts of shapes,
sizes.

20:26.920 --> 20:28.250
It's like
online shopping!

20:28.250 --> 20:30.080
What's the return policy?
[ Laughs ]

20:30.080 --> 20:31.750
Oh, my God.
Principal Ablin!

20:31.750 --> 20:32.750
[ Laughs ]

20:32.750 --> 20:35.420
God,
let's see his pictures.

20:35.420 --> 20:37.330
Holy crap,
he's on a horse!

20:37.330 --> 20:39.670
He is windsurfing
in a shirt and tie!

20:39.670 --> 20:41.170
That is weird!

20:41.170 --> 20:42.620
Let me see
some more.

20:42.620 --> 20:44.210
[ Laughs ]

20:44.210 --> 20:46.210
No! Oh, my God,
you just swiped right.

20:46.210 --> 20:48.120
Is that bad?
What does that
even mean?

20:48.120 --> 20:49.540
[ Laughs ]
It means you're into him.

20:49.540 --> 20:50.710
[ Gasps ]

20:50.710 --> 20:51.920
Katie, I hate you!

20:51.920 --> 20:53.000
[ Cellphone dings ]

20:53.000 --> 20:54.580
Oh, my God,
you matched!

20:54.580 --> 20:56.170
Unmatch! Unmatch!

20:56.170 --> 20:58.210
[ Laughs ]
You can't.

20:58.210 --> 20:59.960
[ Shrieks ]

21:01.710 --> 21:04.710
Hellooo, Doris.

21:04.710 --> 21:07.710
♪♪
